    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p> <p><strong>Bash</strong> the lemongrass stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> with a rolling pin, cut it <span class=\"text-danger\">[them]</span> down the middle lengthways, remove the tough outer layers (keep them for later!) and chop the softer inner stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> finely</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> and finely chop (or grate) the garlic&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Combine</strong> the pork mince, ginger, garlic, inner lemongrass stems, cornflour, soy sauce and sesame oil in a large mixing bowl with clean hands</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> combined, pick up the mixture and slam it down forcefully back into the bowl (this gets rid of any air pockets and brings the mixture together so it holds its shape when cooking)</p> <p><strong>Repeat</strong> until the mixture comes together and becomes sticky and dense</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Divide</strong> the mixture between 10 <span class=\"text-danger\">[20]</span> and shape into balls</p> <p><strong>Refrigerate</strong> until step 7</p> <p><strong>Tip:</strong> chilling the meatballs helps them firm up for cooking&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle for the next step</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, dissolve the stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in 1L <span class=\"text-danger\">[2L]</span> boiled water in a large pot and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, add the rice and outer lemongrass leaves, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 10 min or until the rice is tender</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Chop</strong> the coriander roughly, including the stalks&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Slice</strong> the spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> finely, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the rice is tender, add the shaoxing wine, fish sauce, a big pinch of sugar and 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> more boiled water&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Carefully</strong> drop the meatballs into the stock, then cover and cook for approx. 5-8 min or until the meatballs are cooked through</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/shu-han-lees-khao-tom/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Divide</strong>&nbsp;the meatballs, rice and broth between bowls (remove the lemongrass!)</p> <p><strong>Garnish</strong> with the spring onion and coriander</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
